A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION COMMENDING AND CONGRATULATING MISSISSIPPI'S OWN "FATHER OF WATERS PIPES 
WHEREAS, on August 1, 2001, Articles of Incorporation were filed at the Secretary of State's office, officially establishing "The Father of Waters Pipes 
Having been in existence at
least seven years in an unofficial capacity, this unit has been a regular at many parades, memorials, inaugurations and other similar events.
Individual members have answered the call to play
the immortal tribute when firemen, policemen, game wardens and highway patrolmen lose their lives in the line of duty to this great state; and WHEREAS, the bagpipes have a martial tradition, becoming the only musical instrument in the world to have ever been legally declared a weapon of war.
Today they answer not the call to war,
but the call to honor, to remember, to memorialize, to proclaim and to pay tribute; and WHEREAS, aside from memorials, this unit has been honored to perform at many weddings and has seen many young Mississippians begin their life together, played during the inauguration S. C. R. No. 03/SS02/R543 PAGE 1 521
